description: Times reporters provided real-time analysis of Donald J. Trump’s stunning upset in the presidential election on Tuesday.
title: Election Night Live Coverage
title_page: Election Night Live Coverage - The New York Times
text:
Regarding Indiana, I’m not particularly interested in the results of the presidential race there, but the Senate race — where Evan Bayh, a former Democratic senator, is trying to come back — is pretty fascinating.
We are in New York City tonight, and it was interesting today to see all of these voting sites with huge lines. That is the definition of a symbolic vote — New York State is, of course, not in play. But if Trump loses by a lot here, in the city he calls home, that is certainly worthy of note.
